---
description: Data-driven Godot Resources — stable IDs and content schemas.
globs: ["shahname-td-godot/**/data/**/*.gd", "shahname-td-godot/**/resources/**/*"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Use custom Resource classes (`.gd` + `.tres`) per [README_04](docs/README_04_DEVELOPMENT_PRODUCTION_ROADMAP.md):

- HeroData, TowerData, TowerUpgradeData, EnemyData, WaveData, LevelData / MapData
- ProjectileData, StatusEffectData, RelicData, FateCardData (or BlessingData), ObjectiveData
- ShopItemData, EventData, CosmeticData (meta)

**Rules:**

- Shared `.tres` on disk hold **design defaults only** — no runtime mutable state saved back to disk.
- Copy spawn values into nodes/runtime state at setup.
- **Stable IDs:** `lowercase_snake_case` (`tower_archer`, `enemy_corrupted_jackal`, `card_flame_of_azar`) for save, analytics, and art pipeline — never use display names as IDs.
- `@export_group` / typed `@export` for Inspector clarity.
- Scripts in `scripts/data/`; keep behavior out of resource class definitions.
- Map resources: routes, build_pads, regions, braziers, camera_anchors, sector rules for large maps.

When adding content for Khan 1 only, scope assets to README_01 Phase 1 IDs unless the task explicitly expands campaign.
